#: admin/views/partials/settings-cron-hint.php:15
msgid ""
"Action Scheduler detected — RSS sync runs reliably in the background. "
"Inspect scheduled actions under Tools → Scheduled Actions, group “jardin-"
"toasts” (the menu label may differ if WooCommerce owns Action Scheduler)."
msgstr "Action Scheduler détecté — la synchro RSS tourne en arrière-plan de façon fiable. Inspecte les actions planifiées sous Outils → Actions planifiées, groupe « jardin-toasts » (le label du menu peut différer si WooCommerce possède Action Scheduler)."

#. translators: %s: link to Action Scheduler
#: admin/views/partials/settings-cron-hint.php:22
msgid ""
"WP-Cron with <code>DISABLE_WP_CRON</code> enabled — a system task is "
"triggering WordPress, which is the recommended setup. For even more reliable "
"scheduling you can also install %s."
msgstr "WP-Cron avec <code>DISABLE_WP_CRON</code> activé — une tâche système déclenche WordPress, c’est la configuration recommandée. Pour une planification encore plus fiable, tu peux aussi installer %s."

#. translators: 1: Action Scheduler link 2: wp-config snippet
#: admin/views/partials/settings-cron-hint.php:33
msgid ""
"WP-Cron is driven by site traffic — jobs may be delayed on low-traffic "
"hosts. Install %1$s for a proper queue, or add %2$s to <code>wp-config.php</"
"code> and call <code>wp-cron.php</code> from a real system cron."
msgstr "WP-Cron est piloté par le trafic du site — les tâches peuvent être retardées sur les hébergements peu fréquentés. Installe %1$s pour une vraie file d’attente, ou ajoute %2$s dans <code>wp-config.php</code> et appelle <code>wp-cron.php</code> depuis un vrai cron système."

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:16
msgid "Untappd account"
msgstr "Compte Untappd"

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:17
msgid "Import & sync"
msgstr "Import & synchro"

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:18
msgid "Display & content"
msgstr "Affichage & contenu"

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:19
msgid "Advanced"
msgstr "Avancé"

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:23
msgid ""
"Your RSS URL and username identify the same Untappd account. RSS brings in "
"recent check-ins; a CSV data export (privacy request or Insider archive) is "
"used for full history and complete fields."
msgstr "Ton URL RSS et ton nom d’utilisateur identifient le même compte Untappd. Le RSS apporte les check-ins récents ; un export de données CSV (demande RGPD ou archive Insider) sert à l’historique complet et aux champs détaillés."

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:24
msgid ""
"Scheduled sync reads the public RSS feed. For your complete journal, import "
"the check-ins CSV from Untappd’s data export."
msgstr "La synchro planifiée lit le flux RSS public. Pour ton journal complet, importe le CSV des check-ins depuis l’export de données Untappd."

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:25
msgid ""
"Control how archives look, what gets stored with each check-in, and how "
"ratings map to stars on the front of your site."
msgstr "Contrôle l’apparence des archives, ce qui est stocké avec chaque check-in et la conversion des notes en étoiles côté front."

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:26
msgid ""
"Fine-tune RSS import limits, structured data, notifications, and "
"troubleshooting logs."
msgstr "Affine les limites d’import RSS, les données structurées, les notifications et les journaux de diagnostic."

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:34
msgid ""
"Untappd → WordPress: sync, import, and present your beer journal with theme-"
"friendly templates."
msgstr "Untappd → WordPress : synchroniser, importer et présenter ton journal bière avec des gabarits adaptés au thème."

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:37
msgid "Jardin Toasts settings sections"
msgstr "Sections de réglages Jardin Toasts"

#: admin/views/settings-page.php:64 admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:51
msgid "Save changes"
msgstr "Enregistrer les modifications"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:18
msgid "RSS sync limits"
msgstr "Limites de synchro RSS"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:19
msgid ""
"Caps how many new feed items each scheduled run turns into posts. Extra "
"items stay in a queue and are processed by follow-up cron events."
msgstr "Plafonne le nombre de nouveaux éléments du flux que chaque run planifié transforme en posts. Le surplus reste en file d’attente et est traité par les évènements cron suivants."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:24
msgid "RSS imports per scheduled sync"
msgstr "Imports RSS par synchro planifiée"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:27
msgid ""
"Minimum 1 per run (values below 1 are saved as 1). “Run sync now” uses a "
"higher limit."
msgstr "Minimum 1 par run (les valeurs inférieures à 1 sont enregistrées comme 1). « Lancer la synchro maintenant » utilise une limite plus élevée."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:36
msgid "Sync health"
msgstr "Santé de la synchro"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:37
msgid ""
"Quick signals when diagnosing RSS backlog or incomplete drafts (often RSS "
"items without a rating)."
msgstr "Signaux rapides pour diagnostiquer un backlog RSS ou des brouillons incomplets (souvent des éléments RSS sans note)."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:42
msgid "RSS queue depth"
msgstr "Profondeur de la file RSS"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:46
msgid "Draft check-ins needing data"
msgstr "Brouillons de check-ins en attente de données"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:50
msgid ""
"Recent log lines appear below under “Log file (today)”. Enable debug logging "
"for more detail."
msgstr "Les lignes de log récentes apparaissent ci-dessous sous « Fichier de log (aujourd’hui) ». Active le log de debug pour plus de détail."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:56
msgid "SEO & semantics"
msgstr "SEO & sémantique"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:57
msgid "Optional structured data and microformats for themes and parsers."
msgstr "Données structurées et microformats optionnels pour thèmes et parsers."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:62
msgid "Schema.org JSON-LD"
msgstr "Schema.org JSON-LD"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:67
msgid "Output Review structured data on single check-in pages"
msgstr "Émettre les données structurées Review sur les pages single check-in"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:72
msgid "Microformats"
msgstr "Microformats"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:77
msgid "Add h-entry / e-content classes for IndieWeb-style consumers"
msgstr "Ajouter les classes h-entry / e-content pour les consommateurs IndieWeb"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:89
msgid ""
"Jardin Toasts reads your public Untappd RSS feed and imports check-in CSVs "
"you provide from Untappd’s data export. You are responsible for complying "
"with Untappd’s terms and for content you republish."
msgstr "Jardin Toasts lit ton flux RSS Untappd public et importe les CSV de check-ins issus de l’export de données Untappd. Tu es responsable du respect des conditions d’Untappd et du contenu que tu republies."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:96
msgid "Email notifications"
msgstr "Notifications par e-mail"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:97
msgid "Optional alerts when sync completes or fails."
msgstr "Alertes optionnelles à la fin ou en cas d’échec de la synchro."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:102
msgid "On successful sync"
msgstr "À la fin d’une synchro réussie"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:107
msgid "Email when new check-ins are imported via RSS"
msgstr "Envoyer un e-mail quand de nouveaux check-ins sont importés via RSS"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:112
msgid "On RSS error"
msgstr "En cas d’erreur RSS"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:117
msgid "Email when the feed cannot be fetched"
msgstr "Envoyer un e-mail quand le flux ne peut pas être récupéré"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:122
msgid "Notification email"
msgstr "E-mail de notification"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:125
msgid "Leave empty to use the site admin email."
msgstr "Laisser vide pour utiliser l’e-mail d’admin du site."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:134
msgid "Logging & debug"
msgstr "Logs & debug"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:135
msgid ""
"Verbose logging can help support; keep retention sensible on shared hosting."
msgstr "Les logs verbeux peuvent aider au support ; garde une rétention raisonnable sur un hébergement mutualisé."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:140
msgid "Debug logging"
msgstr "Log de debug"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:145
msgid "Write extra detail to the log file"
msgstr "Écrire plus de détail dans le fichier de log"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:150
msgid "Log retention"
msgstr "Rétention des logs"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:153
msgid "days (0 = disable rotation hints)"
msgstr "jours (0 = désactive les hints de rotation)"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:162
msgid "Log file (today)"
msgstr "Fichier de log (aujourd’hui)"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:163
msgid "Tail of the current log. Paths may differ on your host."
msgstr "Fin du log courant. Les chemins peuvent différer selon ton hébergeur."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:166
msgid "Log output"
msgstr "Sortie du log"

#. translators: %s: directory path
#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:175
msgid "Log directory: %s"
msgstr "Dossier de logs : %s"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-advanced.php:178
msgid "Log directory could not be created."
msgstr "Impossible de créer le dossier de logs."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:40
msgid "Archives & layout"
msgstr "Archives & mise en page"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:41
msgid ""
"Choose how lists of check-ins appear on the main journal and taxonomy pages."
msgstr "Choisis comment les listes de check-ins apparaissent sur le journal principal et les pages de taxonomies."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:46
msgid "Archive layout"
msgstr "Mise en page d’archive"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:49
msgid "Grid — cards with photos"
msgstr "Grille — cartes avec photos"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:50
msgid "Table — compact rows"
msgstr "Tableau — lignes compactes"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:52
msgid ""
"Applies to the beer check-in archive and beer style / brewery / venue "
"listings."
msgstr "S’applique à l’archive des check-ins bière et aux listes par style / brasserie / lieu."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:57
msgid "Public journal URL:"
msgstr "URL publique du journal :"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:68
msgid "Imported content"
msgstr "Contenu importé"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:69
msgid ""
"Control media and taxonomy data saved with each check-in. Check-in notes are "
"stored as post content with automatic paragraphs for plain text."
msgstr "Contrôle les médias et données de taxonomie enregistrés avec chaque check-in. Les notes de check-in sont stockées comme contenu de post avec paragraphes automatiques pour le texte brut."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:74
msgid "Beer photos"
msgstr "Photos de bières"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:79
msgid "Yes — import beer photos into the Media Library"
msgstr "Oui — importer les photos de bières dans la bibliothèque de médias"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:81
msgid "On by default for new installs. Turn off if you only want text."
msgstr "Activé par défaut sur les nouvelles installations. Désactive si tu ne veux que du texte."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:85 includes/class-taxonomies.php:118
#: includes/class-taxonomies.php:126
msgid "Venues"
msgstr "Lieux"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:90
msgid "Yes — create venue taxonomy terms when a location is present"
msgstr "Oui — créer des termes de taxonomie « lieu » quand une localisation est présente"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:92
msgid "On by default. Lets you browse check-ins by place."
msgstr "Activé par défaut. Permet de parcourir les check-ins par lieu."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:96
msgid "Social stats"
msgstr "Stats sociales"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:101
msgid "Yes — store toast counts when Untappd exposes them"
msgstr "Oui — stocker les compteurs de toasts quand Untappd les expose"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:103
msgid "On by default. Optional engagement metadata."
msgstr "Activé par défaut. Métadonnées d’engagement optionnelles."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:107
msgid "Fallback image"
msgstr "Image de repli"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:115
msgid ""
"Use a fallback image when Untappd download fails (on by default). Uncheck to "
"leave the post without a featured image."
msgstr "Utiliser une image de repli quand le téléchargement depuis Untappd échoue (activé par défaut). Décoche pour laisser le post sans image mise en avant."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:117
msgid ""
"Pick a generic beer or logo from your Media Library (no attachment ID to "
"type). There is no built-in remote beer-photo API (keys, licensing, "
"reliability); you can wire Open Food Facts, Wikimedia, or your own source in "
"PHP with the jardin_toasts_placeholder_attachment_id filter "
"(jardin_toasts_placeholder_attachment_id is still fired for backward "
"compatibility), returning a Media Library attachment ID you created."
msgstr "Choisis une bière générique ou un logo dans ta bibliothèque de médias (pas d’ID à saisir). Il n’y a pas d’API distante intégrée pour les photos de bière (clés, licences, fiabilité) ; tu peux brancher Open Food Facts, Wikimedia ou ta propre source en PHP via le filtre jardin_toasts_placeholder_attachment_id (jardin_toasts_placeholder_attachment_id reste émis pour la rétrocompatibilité), en retournant un ID d’attachement créé dans la bibliothèque."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:134
msgid "Ratings & stars"
msgstr "Notes & étoiles"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:135
msgid ""
"Map Untappd’s 0–5 raw score into whole stars. Rules are tested in order; the "
"first matching min/max band wins. The jardin_toasts_rating_rules filter "
"(jardin_toasts_rating_rules is still fired for backward compatibility) can "
"override in code."
msgstr "Convertit le score brut Untappd 0–5 en étoiles entières. Les règles sont testées dans l’ordre ; la première bande min/max correspondante l’emporte. Le filtre jardin_toasts_rating_rules (jardin_toasts_rating_rules reste émis pour la rétrocompatibilité) peut surcharger en code."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:140
msgid "Use mapping rules"
msgstr "Utiliser les règles de mapping"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:145
msgid "Map fractional Untappd ratings to whole stars"
msgstr "Convertir les notes Untappd fractionnaires en étoiles entières"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:152
msgid "Raw score bands"
msgstr "Bandes de score brut"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:153
msgid ""
"Each row is one band: if the raw rating is between min and max (inclusive), "
"it maps to the chosen star level."
msgstr "Chaque ligne est une bande : si la note brute est entre min et max (inclus), elle mappe vers le niveau d’étoile choisi."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:157
msgid "#"
msgstr "#"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:158
msgid "Min (raw)"
msgstr "Min (brut)"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:159
msgid "Max (raw)"
msgstr "Max (brut)"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:160
msgid "Star level"
msgstr "Niveau d’étoile"

#. translators: %d: row number
#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:173
msgid "Band %d min"
msgstr "Bande %d min"

#. translators: %d: row number
#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:177
msgid "Band %d max"
msgstr "Bande %d max"

#. translators: %d: row number
#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:181
msgid "Band %d stars"
msgstr "Bande %d étoiles"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:195
msgid "Labels per star level"
msgstr "Libellés par niveau d’étoile"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:196
msgid ""
"Optional text for each rounded level (for themes, blocks, or future UI)."
msgstr "Texte optionnel pour chaque niveau arrondi (pour thèmes, blocs ou UI future)."

#. translators: %d: star count 0-5
#: admin/views/settings/tab-display.php:205
msgid "%d stars"
msgstr "%d étoiles"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:20
msgid "Diagnostics (DataViews)"
msgstr "Diagnostics (DataViews)"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:21
msgid ""
"Read-only snapshot from current options. Requires a built admin bundle (npm "
"run build in the plugin directory)."
msgstr "Vue en lecture seule des options actuelles. Nécessite un bundle admin compilé (npm run build dans le dossier du plugin)."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:31
msgid "Background RSS sync"
msgstr "Synchro RSS en arrière-plan"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:32
msgid ""
"Scheduled sync reads your public Untappd RSS feed and creates check-in posts "
"from feed items only (beer, brewery, venue, date, and image when present). "
"Ratings are usually missing from RSS — those posts stay as drafts until you "
"enrich them from a full data export CSV."
msgstr "La synchro planifiée lit ton flux RSS Untappd public et crée des posts de check-ins uniquement à partir des éléments du flux (bière, brasserie, lieu, date et image quand présents). Les notes manquent généralement au RSS — ces posts restent en brouillon jusqu’à enrichissement via un CSV d’export complet."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:42
msgid "Enable scheduled RSS synchronization"
msgstr "Activer la synchronisation RSS planifiée"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:45
msgid ""
"Adaptive timing: more frequent when you check in often, lighter when you are "
"quiet."
msgstr "Cadence adaptative : plus fréquente quand tu check-ines souvent, plus légère quand tu es discret."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:58 admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:62
msgid "Run sync now"
msgstr "Lancer la synchro maintenant"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:59
msgid "Fetches the RSS feed immediately (same code path as scheduled sync)."
msgstr "Récupère le flux RSS immédiatement (même chemin de code que la synchro planifiée)."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:70
msgid "Full history: data export (CSV)"
msgstr "Historique complet : export de données (CSV)"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:71
msgid ""
"Request your personal data from Untappd (privacy / GDPR process) or use an "
"Insider subscription export when available. Import the check-ins CSV here — "
"rows are matched by check-in ID and existing posts are updated. No file is "
"sent with “Save changes”; upload runs only when you click Import."
msgstr "Demande tes données personnelles à Untappd (procédure RGPD) ou utilise un export d’abonnement Insider quand disponible. Importe ici le CSV des check-ins — les lignes sont matchées par ID de check-in et les posts existants sont mis à jour. Aucun fichier n’est envoyé avec « Enregistrer les modifications » ; l’envoi ne se fait qu’au clic sur Importer."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:76
msgid "Import check-ins CSV"
msgstr "Importer le CSV des check-ins"

#: admin/views/settings/tab-sync.php:79
msgid ""
"Expected columns include checkin_id, checkin_url, beer_name, brewery_name, "
"rating_score, created_at, comment, venue_name, serving_type, beer_abv, "
"beer_ibu, photo_url (names may vary). Use filters "
"jardin_toasts_gdpr_csv_map_row / jardin_toasts_gdpr_csv_max_rows or "
"jardin_toasts_gdpr_csv_row if your export differs."
msgstr "Colonnes attendues : checkin_id, checkin_url, beer_name, brewery_name, rating_score, created_at, comment, venue_name, serving_type, beer_abv, beer_ibu, photo_url (les noms peuvent varier). Utilise les filtres jardin_toasts_gdpr_csv_map_row / jardin_toasts_gdpr_csv_max_rows ou jardin_toasts_gdpr_csv_row si ton export diffère."

#: admin/views/settings/tab-untappd.php:18
